==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reimburse
<hw>Re`im*burse"</hw> <pr>(-b?rs")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Reimbursed</conjf>
<pr>(-b?rst")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Reimbursing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> +
<ets>imburse</ets>: cf. F. <ets>rembourser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To replace in a treasury or purse, as an equivalent for what has
been taken, lost, or expended; to refund; to pay back; to restore;
<as>as, to <ex>reimburse</ex> the expenses of a war</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make restoration or payment of an equivalent to
(a person); to pay back to; to indemnify; -- often reflexive; <as>as, to
<ex>reimburse</ex> one's self by successful speculation</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Paley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reimbursement</ent>⟦br⟧
